sec.p:
The mean free path (mfp) for charge exchange of ISNs is comparable with the size of the heliosphere (Izmodenov et al. 2000) and the ISNs penetrate through the heliopause (HP) reaching the vicinity of the Sun. The ISNs coming from the undisturbed VLISM are called the “primary” component of the ISNs. Their distribution inside the heliosphere is calculated with the use of the Boltzmann equation for the atom distribution function f(r,v,t)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
