				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$n_{p}V_{p}$\end{document}) through the heliosheath. Black lines represent the magnetic field intensity overlaid on the mass flux. See more in Kornbleuth et al. (2021b)

Moreover, Opher et al. (2020) separated the SW plasma into two ion fluids: thermal SW ions and PUIs created in the supersonic SW. After crossing the TS, the PUIs would be depleted from charge exchange with neutrals originating from the VLISM, which led to a cooling of the heliosheath plasma. The cooler heliosheath led to a shrinking of the heliosphere such that it became smaller and rounder in shape (Fig. 8). Fig. 8
