The shocked SW protons after the passage of the Earth‘s bowshock could act as a diffuse source of H ENAs. However, it requires the terrestrial H-exosphere to extend up to magnetosheath distances of 8 to 10 Earth radii where the shocked SW plasma is present. Recently, Baliukin et al. (2019) derived from SOHO/SWAN Lyman-α\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
